	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001071_0001"/><!--pb/@n='72r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">4<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Aug<hi rend="sup">st</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I have always 
<lb/>thought that <persName>Sir 
<lb/>Roderick</persName> ought 
<lb/>to have all the 
<lb/>honour which 
<lb/>a dedication 
<lb/>could give. <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001071_0002"/><!--pb/@n='72v'--> 
<lb/>only thing which 
<lb/>struck my mind 
<lb/>in addition to this 
<lb/>was that <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Maclear</persName> having 
<lb/>shewn a great 
<lb/>deal of disinterested 
<lb/>kindness - I 
<lb/>perhaps might 
<lb/>make a sort of 
<lb/>double dedication 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001071_0003"/><!--pb/@n='73r'--> 
<lb/>to <persName>Sir R.</persName> &amp; <persName>T. Maclear</persName>
<lb/>but there is no 
<lb/>precedent for 
<lb/>this. Is there? </p>
<lb/><p>I go for <persName>Sir R</persName>
<lb/>at all events. </p>
<lb/><p>I have heard 
<lb/>nothing from 
<lb/>the printers but 
<lb/>sent all the paged 
<lb/>matter &amp; a lot more. </p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001071_0004"/><!--pb/@n='73v'-->
<lb/><p>I was a few days 
<lb/>at a section of the 
<lb/>geological structure 
<lb/>which with the 
<lb/>aid of <persName>Sir R.</persName> is 
<lb/>very good. Wrote 
<lb/>to <persName>Gray</persName> about tsetse 
<lb/>he will get <persName>Ford</persName>
<lb/>to do it. I have 
<lb/>not given the 
<w>con-<lb break="no"/>cluding</w> chapter but 
<lb/>will send in all 
<lb/>the rest speedily. I went 
<lb/>to <persName>Sir H Holland</persName>. Kind regards 
<lb/>
to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Murray</persName><reg>.</reg><persName>D Livingstone</persName></p>
			
